{"id": "EUVD-2017-4697", "enisaUuid": "d2a84dae-33de-304a-a303-ca23c3367f1f", "description": "In the onQueueFilled function of SoftAVCDec, there is a possible out-of-bounds write due to a use after free if a bad header causes the decoder to get caught in a loop while another thread frees the memory it's accessing. This could lead to a local elevation of privilege enabling code execution as a privileged process with no additional execution privileges needed. User interaction is not needed for exploitation. Product: Android. Versions: 6.0, 6.0.1, 7.0, 7.1.1, 7.1.2, 8.0, 8.1. Android ID: A-66969349.", "datePublished": "2018-01-12T23:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-09-16T18:12:49", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://source.android.com/security/bulletin/2018-01-01", "http://www.securitytracker.com/id/1040106", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/102414"], "aliases": ["CVE-2017-13180"], "assigner": "google_android", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "59df6a6f-aeb6-3e1b-a398-b268c36f0733", "product": {"name": "Android"}, "product_version": "7.1.1"}, {"id": "60f78bdd-47dc-3d96-b084-543db2c61959", "product": {"name": "Android"}, "product_version": "6.0"}, {"id": "7a310b0e-9064-3607-96bf-b15417a49ef1", "product": {"name": "Android"}, "product_version": "8.1"}, {"id": "960d6efd-5700-38c2-9306-dcc5034f4dd1", "product": {"name": "Android"}, "product_version": "6.0.1"}, {"id": "c6161570-91ee-364d-995d-acdc588ba3bc", "product": {"name": "Android"}, "product_version": "8.0"}, {"id": "c881ff7f-b197-364e-94f8-a3bf30f8a543", "product": {"name": "Android"}, "product_version": "7.0"}, {"id": "fe5004b3-3a3d-3bfd-a90e-aa10454fd0c5", "product": {"name": "Android"}, "product_version": "7.1.2"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "56c56bf1-042e-3ddb-a654-15c4309c0d84", "vendor": {"name": "Google Inc."}}], "isExploited": false}